The '''Embassy of Sri Lanka in Seoul''' ({{lang-ko|주한 스리랑카 대사관}}) is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Sri Lanka]] to [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Embassy of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka, Seoul, South Korea|url=http://www.mea.gov.lk/index.php/en/missions/99-korea/458-embassy-of-the-democratic-socialist-republic-of-sri-lanka-seoul-south-korea|publisher=[[Ministry of External Affairs (Sri Lanka)]]}}</ref> {{As of|2015}} the ambassador was Tissa Wijeratne, a retired Foreign Service officer.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wijedasa|first=Namini|title=Foreign service or family service?|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/140119/news/foreign-service-or-family-service-80508.html|newspaper=[[The Sunday Times (Sri Lanka)]]|date=19 January 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140118215221/http://www.sundaytimes.lk/140119/news/foreign-service-or-family-service-80508.html|archivedate=18 January 2014}}</ref>After the retirement of the ambassador Tissa Wijeratne, Manisha Gunasekera assumed duties as Sri Lanka’s Ambassador to the Republic of Korea in September 2015.

